                        <h3>Increased complexity of olfactory enrichment improves dementia symptoms.</h3> 
                        Cha, et al. (11) Exposed 34 older adults with dementia to 40 odorants twice a day for 15 days. The control group
                        consisted of 31 individuals with dementia who received no such stimulation. The olfactory-enriched group showed highly significant improvements of up to 300% over controls on 5 different standardized memory tests, and a 325% improvement in depression symptoms. These are remarkable results, and in only 15 days.
                        <br>
                        <br>
                        <h3>Olfactory enrichment at night.</h3>
                        While sniffing 40 odorants twice a day would benefit older adults, it is unlikely that they would be able to open and close 80 sniff bottles each day, as well as to load the bottles into a diffuser device. This problem would be expected to be compounded if people have memory issues or have difficulty opening and closing small bottles. 
                        <br>
                        <br>
                        People, of course, are also busy. It’s hard to remember to do all the self-care people would indeed want. Fortunately, Memory Air® is now designed to present 40 essential-oil odorants sequentially twice nightly. This totals 80 olfactory stimulations without any effort, all while people are sleeping.
                        <br>
                        <br>
                        <h3>An additional benefit: acting younger. </h3> 
                        In a study of 91 participants, Hummel, et. al 2017 found that stimulating older adults with olfactory enrichment led participants to “act” statistically younger than the control group. The enriched group engaged in activities 6 years younger compared to the control group. This was achieved in just 5 months of olfactory enrichment. It appears that olfactory enrichment puts a real bounce in your step. You literally act like a younger person. (80)
