                        <h3>Potential mechanism.</h3> 
                        Sensing pleasant odors suppresses chronic inflammation. More strikingly, even the act of imagining pleasant odors suppresses the immune response, specifically circulating interleukin-2 (46;66). Six months of exposure to menthol odor improved the memory of both young mice and mice that were bred to model Alzheimer’s disease (10). This odor exposure also suppressed inflammation (IL-1b).
                        <br>
