                        We have now identified 139 medical conditions that are accompanied by both olfactory loss and chronic inflammation (44). It may be the case that olfactory loss raises the risk of the developing these medical conditions. It seems possible that olfactory enrichment may improve symptoms of these neurological and somatic medical conditions through a similar mechanism.
